HEADWORD: Outset
<hw>Out"set`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A setting out,
starting, or beginning.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>outset</xex> of a
political journey.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Burke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Giving a proper direction to this <qex>outset</qex> of life.</q>
<rj><qau>J. Hawes.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outsettler</ent>⟦br⟧
